    "summary": "I am motivated and excited about Blended Financing and Development Finance in emerging and developing economies. I have over 10 years of experience in financial management and management of Technical Assistance Facilities in Water & Sanitation Infrastructure Projects and Renewable Energy Projects and 2 years in ESG and Impact reporting.\n\nI help institutions to leverage blended financing mechanisms for investments in water and sanitation, climate change, environmental projects, and infrastructure. Improve evidence-based impact communication, accountability, and transparency through compliance with ESG regulatory requirements and Impact reporting.\n\nMy experience cuts across Project & Financial Management,Technical Assistance, Due Diligence, ESG & Impact management, Capacity building, and Stakeholder Management in the Public and Private sectors.\n\nI have worked closely with Donors/Investors such as the World Bank, KfW, SIDA, DANIDA, BMGF, NDF, EU, AfDB, and FSDA.\n\nIn my spare time, \n\n2009 to date:  I run and hike to support Sports for Change towards Improving the lives of underprivileged bright students in Kenya through education - https://www.sports4change.org\n\n2014: I Co-Founded Kenya Young Water Professionals, a volunteer network that operates under the auspice of the African Water Association (AFWA) in Africa and the International Water Association (IWA) globally. The main goal of the YWP program is to provide an avenue through which the water sector can benefit from the innovative pragmatic and sustainable solutions the youth professionals contribute.\n\n2021: I Founded Friends of Projects-Kenya which is an Initiative focused on catalyzing progress and change in Rural communities to promote sustainability projects related to the alleviation of impacts of Climate change, Gender Equality, and Social Inclusion (GESI). Through a sustainable approach to capacity development, partnerships, and projects. We have raised approximately USD 10,000 for Uvathani Primary School towards the construction of a 6-door Abolution block,2No.10,000Ltrs water tanks, Purchase of 2 No. brick-making machines that save on water and construction materials and the construction of 1 classroom for Uvathani Primary School.",
